      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 15
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sorted 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, featuring the M96 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six and a G96 six-speed manual transaxle. This wide-body example utilizes the Turbo-derived chassis, including the upgraded braking system and AWD viscous coupling for enhanced power delivery. The IMS bearing has been proactively addressed with a ceramic retrofit, and the Variocam Plus system operates flawlessly across the rev range. Recent maintenance includes a high-flow AOS replacement and a complete cooling system refresh to mitigate thermal stress. While the paintwork shows minor road-derived patina, the suspension kinematics remain precise with no bushing deflection. A robust, driver-focused machine for the purist who values mechanical provenance over concours perfection.",
      "price": 32500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 15
    },
    {
